84. Implement a PHP program that creates sessions, sets values in sessions, and removes data from
the sessions.

ANSWER
<?php
// Start the session
session_start();

// Handle session actions based on query parameters
if (isset($_GET['action'])) {
    if ($_GET['action'] == 'set') {
        // Set session variables
        $_SESSION['username'] = 'john_doe';
        $_SESSION['email'] = 'john@example.com';
    }

    if ($_GET['action'] == 'unset') {
        // Remove specific session variable
        unset($_SESSION['email']);
    }

    if ($_GET['action'] == 'destroy') {
        // Destroy the session
        session_unset(); // Unset all session variables
        session_destroy(); // Destroy the session
    }
}
?>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>PHP Session Example</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>PHP Session Example</h2>

    <p><a href="?action=set">Set Session Variables</a></p>
    <p><a href="?action=unset">Unset 'email' Session Variable</a></p>
    <p><a href="?action=destroy">Destroy Session</a></p>

    <h3>Current Session Data:</h3>
    <pre>
<?php
if (!empty($_SESSION)) {
    print_r($_SESSION);
} else {
    echo "No session data available.";
}
?>
    </pre>
</body>
</html>

OUTPUT
PHP Session Example
Set Session Variables
Unset 'email' Session Variable
Destroy Session
Current Session Data:
No session data available.  
